COMMAND
	choff [channel]

DESCRIPTION
	Turn off a communication channel. If a channel is turned off you
	can't send or receive messages on it.
	If the argument is a "*" then all channels will be turned off.
	If no argument was given to the command then all your channels
	will be turned off temporarily and can be turned on again with
	chon.

SEE ALSO
	channels, chon, chwho, =, ==
